    "body": "#### Spark-context\r\n\r\n- spark-3.4: https://github.com/apache/spark/commit/d1ca0ea4ae\r\n\r\n\r\n#### What changes were proposed in SPARK pull request?\r\n\r\n- Change `TakeOrderedAndProjectExec` so that it does not inherit `UnaryExecNode`. Instead make it inherit\r\n  `AliasAwareOutputOrdering`.\r\n\r\n\r\n#### Why are the changes needed in Spark?\r\n\r\nPerformance improvement.\r\nBy inheriting `AliasAwareOutputOrdering`, `TakeOrderedAndProjectExec` can save a sort if the project\r\ninside `TakeOrderedAndProjectExec` has an alias for the sort order.\r\n\r\nExample\r\n\r\n```\r\nval df = spark.range(20).repartition($\"id\")\r\n  .orderBy(\"id\")\r\n  .selectExpr(\"id as c\")\r\n  .limit(10)\r\n  .orderBy(\"c\")\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe execution plan should not include any `SortExec`\r\n\r\n#### Does this PR introduce _any_ user-facing change?\r\n\r\n- No\r\n\r\n#### Why it might affect RAPIDS?\r\n\r\n- Potential optimization that we need to consider on the GPU.\r\n- The execution plan on GPU will have sort that does not appear on the CPU.\r\n\r\n#### Impact on Testing?\r\n\r\nYes.\r\n- Comparing plans between GPU and CPU will be different.\r\n\r\n#### Requires Doc update?\r\n\r\nNo.",
